Get build and test scripts working on Windows (#96)

* Build on windows successfully

When npm runs on windows (even from git bash) it executes scripts as CMD
scripts. Using `$var` in these scripts causes issues on Windows.

Bash can be invoked however, so moving these scripts into shell files in
the bin directory allows the scripts to be completely bash while still
working on windows.

* Cleanup the build-debug and watch script a bit.

Additionally errors are now logged and emitted properly. Also callback is only called when appropriate.

A user may want to handle certain kinds of errors manually, such as
providing a UI for entering proxy information before restarting or
showing a custom error reporting UI.

commit_list.message:
Stability and better error reporting

This was an investigation and attempt to fix issue #30.

It turns out there wasn't actually much to fix, the real issue ended up being a bug in electron version v0.33.1-2 (and possibly some lower versions) desribed in patch notes:

Fix length of Buffer becoming 0 when there are lots of Buffer created.
Fix crash when there is external ArrayBuffer created with pointers to addresses outside the heap.
After updating to latest version of electron the updater started working. This patch actually includes a lot of error propagation and logging improvements however. So I want to wrap this up and get it out.

Sending as a PR for now, in case anyone wants to review or comment. I will merge and publish after a few other fixes.

commit_list.message:
connect.serverClose closes all servers now

The problem was that certain variables were singleton to the module
creating a second server was replacing them and they were not
possible to get a reference to in order to clean it up properly.

This change moves those variables to instance variables on the app
which is stored and then they are all closed when serverClose is
called.
